getAllIndices

public java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> getAllIndices(java.lang.String pinName)
Finds all PinNodes with the pinName as the base name and returns a List of their indices. The base name of a pin is the name without any array references. For example, "my_pin(7)" is a pin name, and "my_pin" is its base name.

Parameters:
pinName - the base name of the pin
Returns:
a List of indices of pins with the base name

getAllPins

public java.util.List<Pin> getAllPins(java.lang.String name)
Returns a list of PinNodes with the same name as the name passed in. Valid names are an exact match (suffix length is zero), or those that are suffixed by an array index (the start of which is marked by an open parentheses character.)

Parameters:
pinName -
Returns:
The list of pin nodes with the same name as pinName.
